<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: brown"><a class="external text" href="../../w/index-title=Portal_Buddhism_Selected_picture_20&action=edit.php.html"><span style="color: brown">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>
<h2 style="font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:brown;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_picture">Selected picture</span></h2>
</div>
<div style="border: 1px solid sandybrown; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: ivory;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">
<div class="center">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:BuddhistTriad.JPG" class="image" title="An early Mahayana Buddhist triad. From left to right, a Kushan devotee, the Bodhisattva Maitreya, the Buddha, the Bodhisattva Avalokitesvara, and a Buddhist monk. 2nd-3rd century CE, Gandhara."><img alt="An early Mahayana Buddhist triad. From left to right, a Kushan devotee, the Bodhisattva Maitreya, the Buddha, the Bodhisattva Avalokitesvara, and a Buddhist monk. 2nd-3rd century CE, Gandhara." src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/BuddhistTriad.JPG/300px-BuddhistTriad.JPG" width="300" height="183" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/BuddhistTriad.JPG/450px-BuddhistTriad.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/BuddhistTriad.JPG/600px-BuddhistTriad.JPG 2x" /></a></div>
</div>
<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">
<tr>
<td width="33%">
<center><small>Credit: <a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:PHGCOM" class="extiw" title="commons:User:PHGCOM">PHGCOM</a></small></center>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b><a href="Mahayana" title="Mahayana">Mahayana</a></b> is one of the two main existing schools of <a href="Buddhism" title="Buddhism">Buddhism</a> and a term for classification of Buddhist philosophies and practice. It was founded in <a href="India" title="India">India</a>.</p>
